CFPB pipeline disabled by takeover on 2026-04-25.

Reason:
  The Schumer Box regex in scripts/pipelines/cfpb/schumer_extractor_v2.py:186-188
  matched non-fee numbers ("12 monthly billing cycles", "Pay Over Time™ APR",
  etc.) and the apply_*.py scripts wrote those values directly to data/cards/*.json
  with `cfpb_verified: true`, overwriting correct human-curated annual_fee values
  for ~24 cards. Production was serving "Amex Platinum annual fee $12" until
  the revert on 2026-04-25.

Until the rewrite is done (see docs/TAKEOVER_PLAN.md, Week 1 section), the
pipeline must not run.

The rewrite must include:
  1. LLM-based extraction (regex has been proven unreliable on real Amex PDFs).
  2. Sanity gates (premium card with annual_fee < $50 → reject, queue for review).
  3. Append-only fact store (Upstash list per card_id × field_path).
  4. Review queue with human approval before promoting facts to data/cards/*.json.
  5. Tests with fixtures of 50+ Schumer Box variants.

To bypass for one run (logged): ALLOW_DISABLED_PIPELINE=1
To re-enable permanently: rm scripts/pipelines/cfpb/_DISABLED.flag
